Description:
Gracious Family Space in the Zone
Period grace meets today's family space in one of the McKinnon Secondary College Zone's premier streets. Beautifully extended to offer a thoroughly contemporary triple zone floorplan, this exceptional four bedroom, 2.5 bathroom home is graced with fine formal lounge and dining rooms (one easily reconfigured to offer a fifth bedroom or home-office), sun-filled family living extending to a soaring al fresco area, and a fan-cooled first-floor lounge as part of the kids' level.
Featuring a quality stainless-steel appliance kitchen and classic bathrooms (including an ensuite) and generous storage (with walk-in and built-in robes plus roof and hallway storage), this accommodating in-Zone home features ducted heating plus reverse-cycle air-conditioning, a beautiful open-fireplace and an auto-gated double garage plus plentiful parking ...all set in around 7750sqft/720sqm gardens with room to play and vegie boxes to harvest!
Just 250m from the back gates of the College, even closer to the bus to Monash University, and a walk to the revitalised Ormond shopping strip and station, this is impressive family living in the heart of the Zone.

Description:
Luxe Appointed, Deco Detailed, In the Zone
With period grace, superb family space and entertaining ease, this one puts McKinnon College Zone living in perfect proportion!
Extended to offer an adaptable up to four-bedroom, two-bathroom family floorplan, this double fronted Art Deco has been sympathetically renovated with superb indoor-outdoor fluidity and the finest of features.
Appointed to an elite standard with CaesarStone benchtops dropping to a waterfall-edge in the state-of-the-art Smeg kitchen (induction cooktop) and a fully tiled ensuite in the master bedroom, this dual zone period home features lofty interior spaces with a formal lounge/4th bedroom, open plan living-dining extending to a vast al fresco area in established gardens and the best design elements of the era (including ornate ceilings, hardwood floors and a fine open fireplace).
With contemporary comforts of central heating and reverse cycle air-conditioning, there's a claw foot bath in the main bathroom, robes in most bedrooms, paintwork for presentation, a euro laundry, ample off street parking and a pull down ladder to a room sized storage loft.
Located minutes from Ormond's transformed station and cosmopolitan strip, moments to a choice of parks and a few doors down from McKinnon Primary School. Land size - 335sqm approx. ALL ENQUIRIES MUST INCLUDE A CONTACT NUMBER.

Description:
Luxurious, Accommodating & Poolside Living
With a choice of station and shopping strip within a stroll, a minute to the back gates of the College and the entrance to Joyce park just around the corner, this prized period home blends exceptional accommodation with state-of-the-art style in arguably the McKinnon College Zones best location.
A superior example of Californian Bungalow with period charm as a backdrop to luxe design, this 5-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom home has been discreetly extended to offer a triple living zone design flowing from formal lounge and dining rooms, to gas log fire-warmed open plan living before spilling out to a huge al fresco area amidst beautifully manicured gardens.
Divinely detailed with high elaborate ceilings, beautiful leadlight and polished Vic Ash timber floors, this high impact home showcases a streamlined CaesarStone and Ilve appliance kitchen, slick modern bathrooms and big robe-fitted bedrooms (including a private ground-floor master-suite).
With every convenience considered, there's ducted heating and evaporative cooling, clever storage (including a workshop plus cubby), 2 water tanks and a well-positioned powder room.
Even the formally landscaped approx 697sqm/7500sqft grounds showcase a superior finish with a solar-heated, salt-chlorinated pool, a designated veggie patch to indulge your green thumb and an abundance of off street parking.
ALL ENQUIRIES MUST INCLUDE A CONTACT NUMBER.

Description:
Quiet convenient 2-bdrm apartment
Secure, peaceful and set to the rear of Acapulco (a block of six) this first-floor apartment presents a first-rate opportunity for owner-occupiers or investors to purchase a low maintenance abode in a location that is convenient to Ormond village shops, cafes and train station, handy to buses on North and Grange roads, near reserves, parks, recreation and schools, and with easy access to Monash University (Caulfield). Carpeted throughout and freshly painted, the apartment is awash in natural light and has a spacious ambience. It provides 2-bedroom accommodation with built-in wardrobes in both bedrooms. There is a Rinnai gas heater and split system AC in the living room. The kitchen has gas cooking, and the bathroom includes laundry facilities. Among the inclusions - intercom entry, and an undercover car space.

Description:
Timeless beauty in a lifetime location
Step from a place of timeless beauty to a world of cutting edge living. Styled to suit a period perfect streetscape of quality renovations and prestige new homes, this high gabled four bedroom, 2.5 bathroom, dual study area home opens wide to offer a contemporary dual living design featuring a fine formal lounge, expansive family living/dining and fitted study nooks on each level.
Designed to fit a modern family with a beautiful bay windowed master suite (with dressing room and dual vanity ensuite), this exceptional home stars a state-of-the-art Siemens appliance kitchen (with steamer and pyrolytic ovens plus gas and induction cooktops), a vast butlers pantry (with custom shelving and room for the fridge), designer bathrooms (with separate WCs) upstairs and down and a fan-cooled al fresco area extending to a wide rear veranda.
With all the latest finishes including European Oak floors, stone benchtops (60mm for the kitchen) and a mix of plantation, shutters, block-out blinds and sheers, there are built in robes and ceiling fans for every bedroom, a ducted vacuum including kick sweep in the butler's pantry and video intercom plus alarm.
With an eye-catching 1200mmm gas log fireplace for the living zone plus reverse cycle ducted heating and air-conditioning over three zones, the home is 6 Star energy rated with double glazing, solar hot water and above-specification insulation. Even the outdoors go above and beyond with a double auto garage including storage and established Manchurian-hedged gardens.
Close to Kilvington Grammar, a walk to Ormond's new station and shopping precinct, this is a timeless beauty with luxury inside and lifestyle all around!
PHOTO ID MUST BE PROVIDED AT ALL OPEN FOR INSPECTIONS

Quality, Lifestyle & a College Zone Address!
Front up to an all-new lifestyle location with streetfront prestige and commuter ease! Description:
Period Beauty, Modern Amenity & on the Strip! Entrance is from Arnott Street.
With period beauty, designer detail and a desirable corner position, this 1920's Art Deco captures the essence of, quality, character and contemporary family living.
A superior example of the era, this 3-bedroom, 1.5-bathroom home also showcases superior styling with a brand new 900mm range stainless steel oven/cooktop and tiled splashback in the modern kitchen, a sleek white bathroom and divine Deco detail (including decorative ceilings, an open fireplace and polished hardwood floors).
Step beyond the home's elaborate Art Deco entrance to find a family functional floorplan featuring separate lounge and dining areas, well proportioned bedrooms and a maintenance free paved courtyard with a north facing aspect.
Appointed with ducted heating, roller blinds and fresh paintwork throughout, the home even provides a separate powder room with laundry facilities, built-in robes and access via Arnott street to a single garage with storage.
With Ormond's cosmopolitan strip and station, Joyce park and Kilvington Grammar school within a short stroll, this is period perfect living in a prestige location. ALL ENQUIRIES MUST INCLUDE A CONTACT NUMBER.

Description:
Classic Californian on 660m2 (approx)!
This fabulous Californian Bungalow on its own 660sqm (approx.) block represents one of the last unrenovated, under capitalised opportunities left in this heritage protected street. Timelessly preserved in all its original glory with high ornate ceilings, glittering leadlight and rustic open fireplace, this classic Californian flows from its relaxing deep verandah, wide entry & fine formal lounge, past three generous bedrooms, vintage bathroom & retro gas kitchen out to vast wrap-around gardens & lock up garage. The convenience can't get much better either, with EE Gunn Reserve at one end of the street and cafes, station & bus links (to Monash Uni or Chadstone Shopping Centre) at the other. A family-friendly, prized Ormond address walking distance to Kilvington Grammar, Ormond Primary, McKinnon Primary or Secondary College & St Kevin's.

Description:
Grandeur, Quality & a Great Address
Find family living on a grand scale at one of Ormond's great addresses. Offering all the living of standalone family home with all the luxury of today's newest developments, this breathtaking four bedroom plus home office, 2.5 bathroom 40sq home meets the demands of today's biggest and most discerning family with a traditional formal lounge with gas-log fireplace, an expansive family zone with 5m of bi-folds to an alfresco area and a versatile lounge at the heart of the first-floor.
Offering a level of quality rarely available to those outside the construction industry, this builder's own home is a showcase of beyond-prestige extras with wine-racking and a fitted butler's pantry for the Miele, De-Longhi and Ilve kitchen, two deluxe fully-tiled dual-vanity bathrooms (ensuite with dual-fitted shower) and a WIR for almost every bedroom (including a bespoke-fitted main dressing-room). With thick stone benchtops (60mm waterfall-edge for the kitchen), plush carpets, porcelain flagstone tiles and Karri timber flooring and William Russell premium timber doors, the home features a spectacular WA Karri, steel and glass staircase, bespoke Emporite and Blum soft-close cabinetry, 2.7m ceilings upstairs and down, hall-storage upstairs and down ...even a laundry chute and double-clothes lines!
Appointed with zoned climate control and alarm, the home is managed by a Hills Home Hub system with sound-wiring, ducted vacuum with 3 kick-sweep outlets and video-intercom. Even the outdoors are grandly appointed with an auto-gated cedar-door double garage with storage and a rear roller-door, exposed aggregate paving, 4000Lwater storage and solar hot-water.
Situated in Ormond's leafiest and loveliest locale within a walk of Kilvington Grammar, the North Rd bus and the revitalised shopping strip and station, this is a grand opportunity!

Description:
Position, peace and security
If you're seeking a contemporary apartment that's secure, serene, smartly styled, and within walking distance of a full range of amenities then you can't go past this property. A tree-lined street is the appealing setting, while the apartment block, with intercom entry and automatic gate to the carport, has attractive garden surroundings. On the first/top floor, this immaculate abode has shiny floorboards, a neutral decor, and sunlight flooding into the open-plan living room via a private balcony with ample space for relaxing outdoors. A split-system A/C keeps the indoor temperature equitable and the chic kitchen has quality appliances, a gas cooktop and a breakfast bar. Both bedrooms have built-in wardrobes, and there is a bright bathroom with laundry facilities. What a lovely, low maintenance lifestyle is offered with this home! Ormond village shops, trains, cafes and buses are within walking distance; recreation, parks and reserves are within handy distance; and there is easy access to Monash Uni (Caulfield) and to Chadstone.

Description:
Exceptional chance to get into McKinnon Zone - Enter off Logan Avenue
Superbly located without having to cross a main road, this gem is within minutes walk to both McKinnon Secondary College and Primary School. First time offered in 76 years, this charming 2 bedroom Art Deco one of a pair in pretty gardens is ready for you to make your mark. Enchanting with its superbly ornate high ceilings, picture rails and lovely character, this homely heartwarmer features a central hall, classic lounge with gas fire, beautiful dining room (fireplace), 2 spacious bedrooms, immaculate original bathroom, updated north facing kitchen with built in breakfast table, separate toilet and laundry. The gorgeous rear garden features a Tuscan style paved alfresco area under a vine-draped cover, and a captivating paved garden courtyard with fishpond. Warm and inviting, this idyllic treasure provides ducted heating, security doors, timber blinds and a large garage off Logan Avenue. In the McKinnon Secondary College zone, metres to McKinnon Primary School, walk to buses, Joyce Park and local cafes.

Description:
A treasure trove of opportunity
In the McKinnon Secondary College zone, this untouched 4 bedroom double fronted Art Deco home is ready to come to life again. Retaining all its period detail, this sun filled charmer features a charming lounge, north facing dining room, 4 well sized bedrooms (3 - BIRs), vintage kitchen with dining booth, a huge sun room, family bathroom, separate laundry & 2nd toilet. On 660 sqm approx with potential to renovate or redevelop (STCA), complete with gas heating, air conditioning, polished boards, a garage with workshop & a shed. A fantastic family location, near Ormond Primary School, restaurants and buses, moments to McKinnon Village, North Road shops & the train.
www.2athompsonstreetormond.com
Todd Newton : 0412 568 313

Description:
Price Reduced! MUST BE SOLD!!
Light and bright with lovely morning light, this first floor 1 bedroom security apartment is comfy cosy at the front overlooking the leafiness of this quiet no through road. Neatly maintained, this original charmer features a casual living area, galley style kitchen with electric cooker and pantry, a double bedroom (BIRs) and ensuite with an updated vanity.
Something to live in or let out, this delightful retreat is jam packed filled with extras including a security door, security intercom, ceiling fan, vertical blinds, external awning, communal laundry for the floor and auto gates to undercover parking. The position is perfect, private and peaceful, yet so close to the new Ormond station, great shops and restaurants, bus to Monash University and beautiful parks.
NOTE: Photos have been digitally furnished for marketing purposes.

Description:
Entry Level In The McKinnon Secondary Zone!
Signature Deco style, matched with previously updated spaces, are the perfect complement to the prominence and convenience of this inviting 2 bedroom, 1 bathroom semi-detached home. Glorious natural light, a fresh feel and beautiful period integrity including warm timber trims and high ornate ceilings enhance lounge and dining rooms, whilst an immaculate kitchen, private courtyard, ducted heating and off street parking add solace to a captivating entry level, downsizer or investment opportunity. Idyllically positioned within the McKinnon Secondary and Primary Zones, moments to McKinnon Reserve, Village and station.

Description:
Pure Potential on a Period Zone Street!
With grand land, a classic Californian and a prized College Zone address, this one takes top marks! Situated on one of the rare streets to combine period living and McKinnon Secondary College Zoning, this approx 703.81sqm property is made even more rare by a 16.15m frontage, an immaculate Californian Bungalow... and endless potential.
Bring your renovation vision to this classic beauty and benefit from a well-maintained and already-extended three bedroom floorplan. With a 1950s extension featuring a time-capsule eat-in kitchen and a sun-bathed window-walled family-room, this solid home is comfortable for today with ducted heating, an air-conditioner, garage, workshop. and ready-to-renovate proportions to step up into a new era of gracious living.
Alternatively, step out the extra-width in this prime site and develop with two streetfront homes to take advantage of a deep northerly aspect, great grounds and this premier College Zone address (Subject to Council approval). Or keep this prime site for a family dream home with room for double-garage, pool and great gardens at this tightly-held address.
